               <interp inst="t18360229-864" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/18360229"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18360229-864" type="date" value="18360229"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18360229-864-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-864-18360229 t18360229-864-offence-1 t18360229-864-verdict-1"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18360229-864-charge-2" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-864-18360229 t18360229-864-offence-1 t18360229-864-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>864. <persName id="def1-864-18360229" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-864-18360229" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-864-18360229" type="surname" value="EVEREST"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-864-18360229" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOSEPH EVEREST</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-864-18360229" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-864-18360229" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-864-18360229" type="surname" value="SHORT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-864-18360229" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM SHORT</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18360229-864-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18360229-864-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18360229-864-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp>stealing on the <rs id="t18360229-cd-170" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360229-864-offence-1 t18360229-cd-170"></join>4th of March</rs> 1 stove, value 20<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and 1 shovel, value 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18360229-name-1279" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1279" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1279" type="surname" value="MILLS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1279" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360229-864-offence-1 t18360229-name-1279"></join>Richard Mills</persName>, in a yacht upon the navigable river Thames.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-1280" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1280" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1280" type="surname" value="CROWNE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1280" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS CROWNE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a shipwright. This property was on board the <hi rend="italic">Maria</hi> yacht, which laid at the back of Mr. Richard Mills's premises, at</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183602290224"></xptr>
               <p>Rotherhithe—he is a shipwright—it is his own vessel this happened—about the 24th of February the yacht was on the river Thames—I am foreman to Mills—the property was in my care—I received information that the stove, and a little patent hearth and shovel, and various articles, were gone from the cabin—I missed it about the 23rd of February—a witness gave me in<lb></lb>formation, and I sent Evans the Thames Police surveyor, and he pro<lb></lb>duced it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BODKIN</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you fitted the stove to the place it was taken from? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; there is no fitting for it—the smoke goes through a funnel—part of the funnel was taken away—it was broken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you any doubt it is the stove? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Not the least; it had been broken and repaired.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-1281" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1281" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1281" type="surname" value="GILES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1281" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN GILES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am engine driver to Mr. Lewis, at Bow. I belong to the ballast engine—this stove came up in Mr. Mackintosh's barge, the <hi rend="italic">Richard</hi>—my steamer laid about two miles from the yacht—they brought the barge up; and they asked my leave to put the stove on board till the barge came back from the barge builders—that was about the 24th of February.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Who do you mean by they? <hi rend="italic">A. Bill</hi> Short; and George Everest—they brought the barge up in the morning—it was day-light when they took the stove out—they brought the barge alongside me—they have been in the habit of bringing barges alongside for two years—I cannot tell whe<lb></lb>ther it was morning, but it was day-light—they put it on board—I have asked them several times since to take it away—I give any of the lighter<lb></lb>men leave to put things on board—Evans took the same stove from my barge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> It was broad day-light? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; there was no concealment—I knew them well before—the barge belongs to Mr. Fuller—they did not mention his name—I know it belonged to him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-1282" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1282" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1282" type="surname" value="NASH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1282" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY NASH</persName>
                  </hi>. I was sleeping forward on board the <hi rend="italic">Maria</hi>, and was awoke by a great noise—I thought it was the police-boat coming on board, and I was afraid to get up, but it was Joseph Everest—he had come in a boat, and somebody else was in the boat—I knew <hi rend="italic">Joe</hi> only by his voice—I said, "Who is that?"—he said, "Bring a lantern"—I said, "It is you, <hi rend="italic">Joe</hi>, you have come to frighten me"—I laid hold of his tarpauling hat, and said, "Joe, is it you? you have come to frighten me?—he jumped out of a sailing boat—I did not see him take any thing; but next morning the stove was missed from the cabin—it was safe overnight.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BODKIN</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Are you what they call a mud-lark? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; I sometimes pick up things in the mud, when I can get nothing else to do—I do not not pick up coals—I pick up iron, bones, and rope—I was afraid the Thames police were coming to take me away to the Thames police-boat—I have never been there; I was sleeping on board that night, because I had no where else to sleep—I knew <hi rend="italic">Joe</hi> by his voice—he said, "Bring the lantern"—I took hold of his hat: I then knew him—I knew him by his voice before—the foreman knew I slept on board this boat—I have slept there two or three months—I knew the stove was there, because I had seen it in the day-time—the cabin doors were open in the day-time—it was about ten o'clock when I went to sleep—I did not see it at night—the foreman missed it next running, or about the middle of the day—I had gone away at day-light—it had not been missed then—I did not know it was gone, when I went away in the morning—I saw the man step out of the boat into a skiff—I did not see any one with him.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183602290225"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-1283" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1283" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1283" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1283" type="given" value="JAMES CHRISTOPHER"></interp>JAMES CHRISTOPHER EVANS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a Thames police officer. I went on board the steam engine barge, and Giles gave me the stove—he told me how he got it—I apprehended short, and asked him how the stove came on board the <hi rend="italic">Two Henrys</hi>—he said he knew nothing about it; but he had seen it on board one of Mr. Mackintosh's barges—I asked Everest how it came there, but he said he knew nothing about it—Short afterwards said he was present when it was put on board the <hi rend="italic">Two Henrys</hi>—that it was Everest put it on board—I afterwards took Everest, and told him it was for a stove stolen from the <hi rend="italic">Maria</hi>—he said he knew nothing about the stove—he had not seen it—I took him to Giles, at the <hi rend="italic">Two Henrys</hi>—he said he was the man who brought it—I said, "What do you say to that?"—he said, "I shall say nothing about it?—I said, "Where did you get the stove from?"—he said, "I shall not tell you where I got it from." (<hi rend="italic">Property produced and sworn to</hi>.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-1284" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1284" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1284" type="surname" value="SHORT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1284" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SHORT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am uncle of one of the prisoners. He works on the river, and has charge of a barge belonging to Mr. Fuller, of Limehouse—in February last that barge wanted repairing, and it was to go to Lime-house-reach, to Mr. Tulley's yard, to be repaired—it was to pass the Gra<lb></lb>vel Engine to get there—I had seen a stove on board that barge for three weeks before the barge went to be repaired—it was not concealed at all—the Gravel Engine is a place where people constantly deposit things—it was not necessary to deposit the stove on board the barge, while it is repaired—it was taken out and left on board the engine, but I do not know who by.</p>
               <p>
